-- Czech Finance Minister Sees Increasing Chance GDP Won’t Contract
-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2012-01-13T07:45:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/czech-finance-minister-sees-increasing-chance-gdp-won-t-contract.html
Czech Finance Minister Miroslav
Kalousek sees increasing chances that the economy won’t contract
this year,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing an interview with
the minister.  Kalousek previously said the economy may contract as much
as 2 percent this year due to the debt crisis in the euro area,
the  Czech Republic ’s largest export market.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
